# ğŸ” Confusion Matrix (Best Model)
This shows how well the model predicted each class.

![Confusion Matrix](images/confusion_matrix.png)

**Interpretation:**  
The model is very strong at identifying **wet** roads, but sometimes misclassifies **dry** roads as wet.  
For safety applications, false-wet predictions are much safer than false-dry, so this bias is acceptable.

---

# ğŸ“Œ Key Takeaways
- AlexNet can learn useful features even from a small dataset.  
- Data augmentation significantly improves accuracy.  
- The model performs best with a lower learning rate.  
- ResNet18 gave slightly better performance than AlexNet.  
- The model is safer when it errs on predicting â€œwet.â€  

